{"id": 19801, "date": "1988-07-31T11:00:00", "date_gmt": "1988-07-31T18:00:00", "guid": {"rendered": "http://estreetshuffle.com/?p=19801"}, "modified": "2026-02-23T15:33:05", "modified_gmt": "2026-02-23T23:33:05", "slug": "matr-joe-grushecky-and-bruce-springsteen-american-babylon", "status": "publish", "type": "post", "link": "https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/1988/07/31/matr-joe-grushecky-and-bruce-springsteen-american-babylon/", "title": {"rendered": "American Babylon"}, "content": {"rendered": "<p>It&#8217;s one of only two songs Bruce <em>didn&#8217;t\u00a0</em>have any involvement with on Joe Grushecky&#8217;s 1995 seminal album.</p>\n<p>The title track to\u00a0<em>American Babylon</em> was all Joe&#8217;s, and he knew it was great when he wrote it. So did Bruce, who upon hearing the demo that Joe recorded on his own with The Houserockers remarked, &#8220;Here&#8217;s your title track.&#8221;</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/it0MaZc8ewg?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p>Although Bruce sings and/or plays on every other track on the album, Bruce convinced Joe that the track was already perfect as recorded&#8211;there was no reason to re-record it.</p>\n<p>But that didn&#8217;t stop Joe and Bruce from performing it live together, which they did when Joe debuted several tracks from his upcoming album at Tradewinds in the summer of &#8217;95&#8230;</p>\n<div id=\"v-SKrUmcO2-1\" class=\"video-player\"><iframe title='VideoPress Video Player' aria-label='VideoPress Video Player' width='758' height='568' src='https://videopress.com/embed/SKrUmcO2?hd=1&amp;cover=1&amp;loop=0&amp;autoPlay=0&amp;permalink=1&amp;muted=0&amp;controls=1&amp;playsinline=0&amp;useAverageColor=0&amp;preloadContent=metadata' frameborder='0' allowfullscreen data-resize-to-parent=\"true\" allow='clipboard-write'></iframe><script data-jetpack-boost=\"ignore\" src='https://s0.wp.com/wp-content/plugins/video/assets/js/next/videopress-iframe.js'></script></div>\n<p>&#8230;and for all six nights of Joe&#8217;s &#8220;October Assault&#8221; mini-tour following the album&#8217;s release.\u00a0Bruce was an honorary Houserocker for the entire tour, and &#8220;American Babylon&#8221; featured prominently at the heart of the set every night.</p>\n<p>Opening night at The Stone Pony was captured for posterity on <em>American Babylon: Live at the Stone Pony</em>, one of the rarer officially released live Springsteen recordings (even if it&#8217;s actually Joe&#8217;s show). Bruce&#8217;s backing vocals may not be audible in the mix, but he definitely makes his presence known on guitar.</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/Z0o2Sx55fRs?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p>Bruce and Joe have shared a stage together many times since, but after a one-off appearance in Pittsburgh in 1998, &#8220;American Babylon&#8221; dropped out of rotation as one of their go-to on-stage collaborations.</p>\n<p><strong>American Babylon<br />\nFirst Performed:</strong> July 22, 1995 (Sea Bright, NJ)<br />\n<strong>Last Performed:</strong> March 2, 1998 (Pittsburgh, PA)</p>\n<p>\u00a9 December 11, 2020</p>\n", "protected": false}, "excerpt": {"rendered": "<p>American Babylon&#8217;s title track is one of the only tracks Bruce had nothing to do with on the album, but that hasn&#8217;t stopped Bruce and Joe from teaming up to play it on stage.</p>\n", "protected": false}, "author": 1, "featured_media": 22627, "comment_status": "open", "ping_status": "open", "sticky": false, "template": "", "format": "standard", "meta": {"_monsterinsights_skip_tracking": false, "_monsterinsights_sitenote_active": false, "_monsterinsights_sitenote_note": "", "_monsterinsights_sitenote_category": 0, "jetpack_post_was_ever_published": false, "_jetpack_newsletter_access": "", "_jetpack_dont_email_post_to_subs": false, "_jetpack_newsletter_tier_id": 0, "_jetpack_memberships_contains_paywalled_content": false, "_jetpack_memberships_contains_paid_content": false, "footnotes": "", "jetpack_publicize_message": "", "jetpack_publicize_feature_enabled": true, "jetpack_social_post_already_shared": true, "jetpack_social_options": {"image_generator_settings": {"template": "highway", "default_image_id": 0, "font": "", "enabled": false}, "version": 2}}, "categories": [4, 3612, 5], "tags": [269, 56], "class_list": ["post-19801", "post", "type-post", "status-publish", "format-standard", "has-post-thumbnail", "hentry", "category-cover-me", "category-great", "category-meeting-across-the-river", "tag-american-babylon", "tag-joe-grushecky"], "aioseo_notices": [], "jetpack_publicize_connections": [], "jetpack_featured_media_url": "https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/american-babylon.jpg?fit=1280%2C720&ssl=1", "jetpack_sharing_enabled": true, "jetpack_shortlink": "https://wp.me/p9w3Lk-59n", "jetpack_likes_enabled": true, "jetpack-related-posts": [{"id": 29192, "url": "https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/1988/08/17/matr-joe-grushecky-and-bruce-springsteen-is-she-the-one/", "url_meta": {"origin": 19801, "position": 0}, "titl